title.narrative: Seed producer organizations implementing Cooperative Development Plans within project context

comment.narrative: As per the AF project paper
Target achieved
39 PDCs were financed by the project. Some organizations were able to present two PDCs in different sowing seasons.
As per the AF project paper
Target achieved
2,403 Ha/year of project implementation
As reported in the AF project Paper
The project was able to respond to market signals for an increased production of beans seed, given the higher internal and externaldemand.
2720 MT of certified bean seeds, of which 869 MT were financed in the ongoing 2014 primera sowing cycle. Beans account for 70percent of total seed production supported by the project.
As reported in the AF project Paper
The demand for certified maize seed has been much lower than expected. Reasons to be further assessed in the final report and theICR.
Additional 244 MT: 55 MT were produced in 2013 while 189 MT are financed for production in the current 2014 primera sowing season.
As reported in the AF project Paper
Final figure to be updated in the ICR.
Production of the first 920 MT of rice seed is being financed at the moment and would be certified in a few months.

title.narrative: Cumulative incremental production of certified basic grain seed

comment.narrative: As reported in the AF project paper

At the moment, the target is achieved at 77 percent as MAGFOR reports that 1,978 MT of seed are yet in production at the end of theproject and would be certified for commercialization during the grace period. To be reported in the ICR and the final projectreport.

Actual data reflects only the confirmed production of 2013. in 2013, 1907 MT were produced and certified. In the current 2014primera sowing season, another 1,978 MT are being produced for certification. Note that breakdown indicators per type of grain arereported below with 2013 and 2014 data.

title.narrative: Cumulative incremental production of genetic, foundation, and registered basic grain seed

comment.narrative: As reported in the AF project paper
Target achieved at 71 percent. Given the production of registered seeds by private producers, INTA did not need to increase its ownproduction as initially planned.
460 MT of high quality seed have been produced to respond to the actual demand from producers of certified seeds.
